<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" Description="VolumeGroups organize similar audio streams together under a common volume index. Since users may move through the various VolumeGroups supporting the Mutex Sink, with the possibility of each volume group being at a different step of the index, it is import to ensure that these transitions produce a pleasing audio experience. To facilitate this, the calibrateable ramp times are used to define the mute/unmute ramp rates used when an audio stream is activated or deactivated according to their VolumeGroup.">
  <CalDefFileVersion>1</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>6/13/2019</Date>
    <Description>Per CR#2060763 AOSP transition, Created new calibration for AOSP. Add MUTE &amp; UNMUTE RAMPS for VOICE, MISCELLANEOUS, HIGHPRIORITY volume groups to existing groups, entered default values, Set usages.</Description>
    <Author>Christine Marzan</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
